# initial_program.py

import random

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START
def run_search():
    n = 47
    # all grid points
    grid = [(x,y) for x in range(n) for y in range(n)]
    S = []
    random.shuffle(grid)
    for (x,y) in grid:
        # check collinearity against every pair already in S
        is_collinear = False
        if len(S) > 1:
            for i in range(len(S)):
                x1, y1 = S[i]
                # Check collinearity with the new point (x, y) and every other point in S
                for j in range(i + 1, len(S)):
                    x2, y2 = S[j]
                    # Check if the new point is collinear with (x1, y1) and (x2, y2)
                    if (y2 - y1) * (x - x1) == (y - y1) * (x2 - x1):
                        is_collinear = True
                        break
                if is_collinear:
                    break
        if not is_collinear:
            S.append((x, y))
    print(len(S))
    return S
# EVOLVE-BLOCK-END
